{{one source|date=February 2013}} {{Infobox Airline | airline = Air 26 | logo = Air 26 logo.png | logo_size = | fleet_size = 6 | destinations = | IATA = - | ICAO = DCD<ref name="aerotransport">[http://aerotransport.org Information about Air 26 at the Aero Transport Data Bank]</ref> | callsign = | parent = | company_slogan = | founded = 2006 | headquarters = [[Luanda]], [[Angola]] | key_people = | hubs = [[Quatro de Fevereiro Airport]] | secondary_hubs = | focus_cities = | frequent_flyer = | lounge = | alliance = | website = www.air26.co.ao <small>(defunct)</small> }}
'''Air26 - Linhas Aéreas, S.A.''' is an [[airline]] based in [[Luanda]], [[Angola]]. Founded in 2006, it operates domestic passenger and cargo flights{{citation needed|date=February 2013}} out of the city's [[Quatro de Fevereiro Airport]].<ref name="aerotransport"/> Along with all other Angolan airlines except for [[TAAG Angola Airlines|TAAG]], Air 26 is [[List of air carriers banned in the European Union|banned]] from operating within the [[European Union]]. In 2010, the company had its [[Air Operator's Certificate|licence]] revoked, but it was re-issued on 31 January 2011.<ref name="aerotransport"/>
