'''Banque Internationale du Bénin''' ('''B.I.B.E.''') is a national [[bank]] of [[Benin]]. It is a member of the [[West African Bankers' Association]].

It has its headquarters at Carrefour des 3 Banques in [[Cotonou]] but also has branches in [[Porto-Novo]] and [[Parakou]]. [[Nigeria]] dominates the bank, with the First Bank of Nigeria Plc. having a 13.6% share, the  Union Bank of Nigeria Plc. (13%), Nigerian Economic Operatives (47.7%), Nigerian Bureau of Public Enterprises  (6.7%), and then the First Interstate Merchant Bank Ltd. (11.1%) and finally the Beninese Economic Operatives with 8.2%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wabao.biz/home/waba/bank_benin.html |title=List of banks in Benin |publisher=West  African  Bankers' Association |accessdate=January 11, 2009 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080926020442/http://www.wabao.biz/home/waba/bank_benin.html |archivedate=September 26, 2008 }}</ref>

