{{for|the 1972 Croatian film|The Living Truth}} {{primary sources|date=September 2017}} {{Infobox TV channel | name =Živa istina | logofile = | logosize = 200px | logoalt = | logo2 = | launch = March 2002 | closed date = | picture format = | share = | share as of = | share source = | network = [[Prva Srpska Televizija|''TV Prva'' (Montenegro)]], [[Radio Antena M|''Antena M'']] | owner = [[Darko Šuković]] | slogan = | former slogan = | country = [[Montenegro]] | broadcast area = [[Montenegro]] | headquarters = [[Podgorica]] | former names = | sister names = | timeshift names = | web = [https://antenam.net/ziva-istina Živa istina] | sat serv 1 = | sat chan 1 = | sat serv 2 = | sat chan 2 = | cable serv 1 = | cable chan 1 = | sat radio serv 1 = | sat radio chan 1 = | adsl serv 1 = | adsl chan 1 = | online serv 1 = | online chan 1 = }}
'''''Živa istina''''' ([[English language|eng. translat.]] ''Whole truth'') the most influential political [[talk show]] in [[Montenegro]]. Occasionally, guests are scientists, artists, sportsmen, as well. The editor and host is [[Darko Šuković]].
From March 2002 to April 2012, ''Živa istina'' has been [[broadcasting]] on ''[[TV IN]]''. Next seasons were simultaneously shown on [[RTV Atlas|''TV Atlas'']] and [[Prva Srpska Televizija|''TV Prva'']], and from September 2017 it is [[broadcast]] only on [[Prva Srpska Televizija|''TV Prva'' (Montenegro)]].
From the very beginning, ''Živa istina'' is produced by [[Radio Antena M|''Antena M'']], which [[broadcast]]s the talk show through its [[radio program]]. The new air term of ''Živa istina'' is Sunday from 14 P.M.
There is almost no significant politician from the former [[SFRY]] who was not a guest in the ''Živa istina'' ([[Milan Kučan]],<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=akdSVrarm5M ''Živa istina'', guest Milan Kučan(2013)]</ref> [[Stjepan Mesić]],<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KYxHxTJQpjw ''Živa istina'', guest Stjepan Mesić (2013)]</ref> [[Raif Dizdarević]], [[Haris Silajdžić]], [[Ejup Ganić]], [[Milorad Dodik]], [[Zoran Đinđić]], [[Vojislav Šešelj]],<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GIa6oMR3Tes ''Živa istina'', guest Vojislav Šešelj (2013)]</ref> [[Vuk Drašković]], [[Boris Tadić]], [[Aleksandar Vučić]], [[Ramush Haradinaj]]<ref>[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GAJ7CiF_v7k ''Živa istina'', guest Ranush Haradinaj (2013)]</ref>...)
Some of the guests in the show were: [[Robert Gelbard]], [[Miroslav Lajčak]], [[Horhe Kapetanić]] and each of [[Montenegrins (ethnic group)|Montenegrin]] political [[leader]]s.
As a matter of fact, ''Živa istina'' is the only political talk show who hosted all leading politicians of its time.
